<TITLE> Lifting emergency depends on normalcy: Matin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 25 (bdnews24.com)  The lifting of the state of emergency depends on normalcy of situation, said home adviser M A Matin Tuesday. "Lifting of the state of emergency is a government decision. I am just a part of the government and cannot tell you anything with certainty," he told reporters after a meeting of the sensational cases monitoring committee. He said that the law and order situation of the country has become "normal" but stressed that to maintain social order, assistance of all quarters is required. "To prevent mugging, robbery and crimes during Eid, steps have also been taken," said Matin. "If necessary, security vigilance will be tightened." Home secretary Abdul Karim, Dhaka city police commissioner Naeem Amhed, director general of RAB Khondokar Hassan Mahmud and other officials were present at the meeting. bdnew
